STRING
It is an object that represents sequence of characters
In Java, String is an immutable object
String is a class that presents in java.lang.string package
CharSequence is the main parent interface of string
CharSequence interface was implemented by String, StringBuffer and StringBuilder

String can be declared by two ways. 1. String literal 2. String new keyword
Using string literal we can save memory as new keyword create another new block in heap memory


STRINGBUFFER
StringBuffer is a mutable object
It is also a child class of Charsequence Interface
It is Synchronised and does not support multi-threading
Stringbuffer can be declared by only new keyword

STRINGBUILDER
StringBuILDER is a mutable object
It is also a child class of Charsequence Interface
It is NOT Synchronised and does support multi-threading